The paper discusses the development of a controller for unmanned aerial vehicles (UAVs), which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The use of advanced planning and navigation algorithms also suggests the involvement of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and control systems (cs.SY). The paper also mentions obstacle avoidance, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) research.
